        <h1>Our Mission</h1>
        <div class="image">
            <div class="chloe">
                <img src="\images\PFP\Chloe_Cho.webp" alt="">
            </div>
            <div class="text">
                <h5>My name is Chloe Cho, and I am currently a high school junior at Bergen County Academies, majoring in the Academy of Visual and Performing Arts-- music concentration. I founded Solis and Luna Arts, which was inspired by my grandfather. My grandfather was a veteran of the Vietnam War who had suffered from numerous physical and health ailments. I have many memories of my grandfather struggling to sleep and take care of himself because of past events in the war. But during my childhood, my mother had suggested something— to play music for him. The first piece I played for him was my own rendition of “Can’t Help Falling in Love,” by Elvis Presley. I remember all the emotions I felt after that little performance, as I saw the tears decorate my grandfather’s face. Playing for him turned into a weekly schedule. Every Sunday, after he came back from church, I’d give him a short performance before dinner time. But one day, that schedule changed a little. He started to join me in playing. Seeing how much music was able to transform my grandfather had inspired me to start playing music for others, and eventually led to the creation of Solis and Luna Arts.</h5>
                <h6>- Chloe Cho</h6>
            </div>
        </div>
        
